Your lawyer might want you to get a DUI evaluation before your plea. You should downplay how much you drink to save money on the classes. You only drink for holidays and celebrations like birthdays, about 2-3 times a month, and only drink about as many drinks when you do.

If your BAC is .16+ they'll likely be harsher and probe you for the honesty portion (if they think you're lying they could make you pay for another evaluation) so, in that case the day you got your DUI you drank more than usual and won't do so again. You might have to answer a multi choice quiz about your drug use: you never tried any other drugs, only alcohol (hopefully they don't have evidence of other drug use)

Check out r/dui on reddit, there's a lot of people who share their stories there and their experiences are helpful to make the process easier.

Get a breathalyzer and don't drive unless you blow 0s. Also, if you smoke weed they started enforcing DUIs for that. My counselor said a guy hit a woman who was running across a dark street at night and they were pretty harsh to him for that because he smoked enough earlier that day for them to charge him with a DUI for that (complete freak accident, she jumped out in front of his car like a deer, but the state wanted their money)
